@lukehoban this can technically impact people. It's a source break, but not a binary break.  Specifically, you might imagine someone writing:

```ts
const v: ProviderResource | undefined = res.getProvider(...);
```

Because this returns a broader set of values, this can cause a source break later.  Note: it would not be a binary break because this will still only ever return `ProviderResource` instances until the user *explicitly* starts passing along `ProviderRef`s.

