Some details for refactoring Scalar and Histogram use the same notion of Scale: 
This is most unlikely and it gets things pretty complicated. The scalar and histogram data type was designed (by stephanlee) differently for a reason. The runs on scalar have different set of steps while there is only one set of steps on histogram. 
In our demo data, all demo runs have the same set of steps, they all have data on step, say, 100 and non on step 101 etc. Yet in reality, users data could be more like run1&2 have data on step 100,103 while run3 have data on step 101,102,103. 
